Description: Fragment of handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light buff-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Agesippos. Trimmed. An unpublished example is from the same die, Athenian Agora SS8181. Closely related is Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0037.05.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0619)
